Now, we can use the Fundamental Theorem of Calculus, which states that if $f$ is continuous on $[a, b]$ and if $F$ is an antiderivative of $f$ on $[a, b]$, then $\int_{a}^{b} f(x) \mathrm{dx} = F(b) - F(a)$.
